      <lg xml:id="TolE0224">
<l>āvu māvum viḷippeyark kiḷaviyum</l>
<l>yāveṉ viṉāvum palavaṟ ṟiṟutiyu</l>
<l>mēval kuṟitta vuraiyacai miyāvun</l>
<l>taṉṟoḻi luraikkum viṉāviṉ kiḷaviyō</l>
<l>ṭaṉṟi yaṉaittu miyalpeṉa moḻipa</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The words <foreign xml:lang="ta">ā</foreign> ' cow ' and <foreign xml:lang="ta">mā</foreign> ' beast ', nouns in vocative,</l>
<l>the interrogative <foreign xml:lang="ta">yā,</foreign> the ending [<foreign xml:lang="ta">ā</foreign>] of non-personal [plural finite verbs],</l>
<l>the expletive particle <foreign xml:lang="ta">miyā</foreign> denoting command,</l>
<l>[and] interrogative words denoting the action of the speaker</l>
<l>[have] no [change] ; all such [expressions] [have] the natural joining ; thus it is said.<note place="foot">Exx. : <foreign xml:lang="ta">ā ciṟitu </foreign>' the cow is small ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">mā tītu </foreign>' the beast is evil ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">urā
                cel </foreign>' go, villager ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">yā ciṟiya</foreign> ' which things are small ? ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">uṇṇā kutirai</foreign> ' horses don't eat ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">kēṇmiyā koṟṟā</foreign> ' listen, koṟṟa ! ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">uṇkā tēvā </foreign>' will I eat, o god ? ' (accord. to Nacc. : <foreign xml:lang="ta">yān uṇpēṉō).</foreign></note>
<l>[have] no [change] ; all such [expressions] [have] the natural joining ; thus it is said.<note
              place="foot">Exx. : <foreign xml:lang="ta">ā ciṟitu </foreign>' the cow is small ', <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">mā tītu </foreign>' the beast is evil ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">urā
                cel </foreign>' go, villager ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">yā ciṟiya</foreign> ' which things are small ? ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">uṇṇā kutirai</foreign> ' horses don't eat ', <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">kēṇmiyā koṟṟā</foreign> ' listen, koṟṟa ! ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">uṇkā tēvā </foreign>' will I eat, o god ? ' (accord. to Nacc. : <foreign xml:lang="ta">yān uṇpēṉō).</foreign></note></l>
<l>[In] the compounds of two words<note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">irupeyarttokaimoḻi,</foreign> corresp. to Skt. <foreign xml:lang="sk">dvandva.</foreign></note> [with] <foreign xml:lang="ta">um</foreign> removed,</l>
<l><foreign xml:lang="ta">a</foreign> is in fact inserted.<note place="foot">E.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">arāapāmpu</foreign> ' snake [and] serpent ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">irāapakal</foreign> ' day [and] night '.</note></l>
      </lg>
